26/04/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A campaign in support of establishing a regional commission for truth-seeking and truth-telling about war crimes committed in the former Yugoslavia kicks off on Tuesday (April 26th). 
A coalition of several NGOs will collect signatures for the initiative in eight cities across the region. 
The campaign, called "One million signatures for RECOM", will be held in Belgrade, Zagreb, Sarajevo, Banja Luka, Ljubljana, Pristina, Skopje and Podgorica, and will end on June 6th. 
(Beta, B92, Tanjug - 26/04/11)
